title: Nokia's new sale strategy bets on re-launch of '3310' | Zee News
text:
Follow @ZeeNews 
New Delhi: In order to encash once again the popularity of its iconic 3310 mobile phone model, Finnish mobile phone maker Nokia is reportedly set to re-launch the sturdy cellphone model. 
As per report in VentureBeat, the model will be re-launched at the Mobile World Congress in Barcelona later in February. 
The report further adds that the phone may be sold for 59 euros (approximately Rs 4,200). First Published: Wednesday, February 15, 2017 - 10:16 More from zeenews
